        {
            System.out.print(arr[i] + " ");
        }   }     }

13.	TWO POINTER:          

--> 2 pointer = “TWO PEOPLE WALKING”

--> Imagine:   One person at start (left),  One person at end (right) 

--> [ 1   2   3   4   6 ]
  L               R

--> MAIN IDEA:               CHECK → MOVE POINTERS

--> GOLDEN RULE:      If sum small → move LEFT →                                  If sum big   → move RIGHT ←

--> WHEN TO USE TWO POINTER?
•	Sorted array                         Pair / sum problem
•	Remove duplicate.               Reverse array

--> TYPES OF TWO POINTER
a.	Type 1: Opposite direction                  left → ← right
b.	Type 2: Same direction                     left → right →

--> Used in:
a.	Remove duplicates                            
b.	Move zeros 

--> FORMULA
1. Take left & right
2. Check condition
3. Move pointers

14.	Largest Subarray Sum (Kadane’s Algorithm)
--> Formula:            sum += arr[i]            if sum < 0 → reset
public class LargestSubArray
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        int[] arr = {10,20,30,40,50,80};
        int sum = arr[0];
        int max = arr[0];
        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) 
        {
            if (sum + arr[i] > arr[i]) 
            {
                sum = sum + arr[i];
            } 
            else 
            {
                sum = arr[i];
            }
            if (sum > max) 
            {
                max = sum;
            }    }
        System.out.println(max);
    }   }
